 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Dalamarn Darkgem</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> As stated, CoC, and Ebolt are great.  The undead slow has massive taunt if you happen to be fighting undead.  Insideous retro seems to have less argo than ignite bones.  Ignite blood and Splurt have large taunt if allowed to run their duration.  Like some mentioned earlier, I prefer sit-taunting.  Get argo, when he stops following you and hits pet just sit down.  He will come for you, stand up and he will turn back to pet.  Run a little ways and sit again.  If he doesn't come after you, stand up, nuke him, and sit back down.  You can lead him around by the nose like this.  It's a lot more precise than fear kiting to control a mob's movements.</P><P> </font></td>
